Their blooming tea is the best tea I have been had. So far I have had their veggie ramen, kimchi ramen and their vieja ropa udon, plus some appetizers. Great food. Great for comfort on a snowy or windy day. Great always.

Absolutely amazing food. This month they had cuban fusion and my God, it was spot on. The drinks were amazing, the ramen was superb... loved it all! What's really awesome was the service. The waiter checked up on us all the time and he was so damned friendly!  I'll be coming back.

Holy cow, this place does the best ramen I have ever had. I have had a few different ramens in varying quality, but Tori Tomo is the best.  Also, unlike Ganko, there are a few vegetarian and chicken options - you aren't forced to have pork!  Overall great experience ordering and picking up. I can't wait to dine in person one day!

Mouthwatering ramen. I first tried the pork broth ramen; it was a nice, rich, creamy broth. I also recently had the kimchi broth ramen, which I recommend to kimchi jiggae lovers out there. Not very spicy with a savory/sweet broth. Every spoonful is full of umami flavor. A great spot if you want a warm and hearty meal.
